WEBVTT

00:02.003 --> 00:03.288
JAMES: Previously on
12 Monkeys...

00:03.379 --> 00:06.462
JAMES: For you
to create time travel,
you had to lose Hannah.

00:06.549 --> 00:08.039
Or at least
believe that you did.

00:08.384 --> 00:09.624
Dad?

00:09.719 --> 00:10.708
(GUNSHOT)
(GRUNTS)

00:12.471 --> 00:14.962
Even ifyou stop them,
I could just make it again.

00:15.308 --> 00:16.639
I’m too dangerous alive.

00:16.726 --> 00:19.183
You need to get out
of here, find a hole,
and disappear into it.

00:20.354 --> 00:21.560
(MUFFLED GRUNT)
You're insane.

00:21.647 --> 00:23.353
Initiate Splinter Sequence.

00:23.900 --> 00:25.481
It works?
Oh, yeah.

00:25.568 --> 00:26.557
This is my life's work.

00:26.694 --> 00:30.312
CASSIE: When he was
in my head, I saw
a place called Titan.

00:30.406 --> 00:32.897
You and I,
we can go there together.

00:33.034 --> 00:34.820
We kill The Witness.

00:35.661 --> 00:37.572
JENNIFER: What's the natural
predator of the monkey?

00:37.830 --> 00:38.819
Hyena!

00:38.915 --> 00:40.155
We'll take the fight
to them, Cassie!

00:40.249 --> 00:42.240
We have to go Monkey hunting.

00:43.586 --> 00:45.247
(WIND WHOOSHING)

00:46.923 --> 00:47.912
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

01:12.448 --> 01:13.779
(WHISTLING)

01:26.587 --> 01:27.963
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

01:32.301 --> 01:34.963
JENNIFER: Hiya, Tall Man.
Get my note?

01:35.763 --> 01:37.628
PALLID MAN: Jennifer?

01:37.723 --> 01:39.054
JENNIFER: I want you to
take this moment,

01:39.141 --> 01:41.803
and think back
to the day we met.

01:41.894 --> 01:43.885
To the person I was then.

01:43.980 --> 01:46.972
Crazy, wild-eyed,
Jennifer Goines.

01:49.819 --> 01:50.729
(GUN COCKS)

01:50.820 --> 01:51.809
(GUNSHOT)

01:52.488 --> 01:54.149
Well, the good old days
are over.

01:54.490 --> 01:55.479
I’m not a victim anymore.

01:55.574 --> 01:56.563
Hey.

01:56.659 --> 01:59.241
I’ve got
credit cards and the Second
Amendment on my side.

01:59.328 --> 02:00.317
I’m free.

02:00.413 --> 02:03.826
Like a virus in a preschool,
l’m paying it forward
to all the other crazies.

02:04.166 --> 02:07.158
I’ve got the keys to
the zoo and now I’m
springing the cuckoo’s nest.

02:07.670 --> 02:10.002
There's a new pack in town.

02:10.089 --> 02:12.671
Predators with a purpose
and a thirst for vengeance.

02:12.758 --> 02:14.589
Because there’s one
thing I’ve learned,

02:14.677 --> 02:18.340
is that nothing
frees you to be crazy
like learning that you’re not.

02:20.599 --> 02:23.511
My whole life,
people tried to use me,

02:23.686 --> 02:26.598
break me, shape me,
mold me into not me.

02:28.024 --> 02:30.265
Daddy had that
doctor lock me away.

02:30.359 --> 02:33.021
My father wasn’t the only one
he was working for, was he?

02:33.112 --> 02:34.477
(GRUNTS)

02:35.323 --> 02:36.438
Mmm-mmm.

02:37.158 --> 02:40.275
You tried to lock
me in a cage, too.

02:40.369 --> 02:41.529
Like an animal.

02:44.373 --> 02:45.874
So I became one.

02:45.958 --> 02:46.947
(FRENZIED LAUGH)

02:47.668 --> 02:49.784
Guess which animal / became.

02:49.879 --> 02:51.619
Guess. Here’s a hint.

02:51.714 --> 02:53.875
Of all creatures,
great and cuddly,

02:53.966 --> 02:56.548
which is the natural
predator of the monkey?

02:56.802 --> 02:57.791
(JENNIFER LAUGHS)

02:58.179 --> 02:59.544
The hyena.

03:00.014 --> 03:02.471
These are the end times,
Tall Man.

03:02.558 --> 03:03.968
But not for humanity.

03:04.060 --> 03:05.846
I’m coming for you.

03:32.254 --> 03:34.506
(THUNDER RUMBLING)
WHITLEY: Scouting team
took these.

03:36.008 --> 03:39.921
MiIIburn Survivors camp,
just north of us,
about a week ago.

03:41.555 --> 03:45.343
The same camp,
three hours ago.

03:54.276 --> 03:55.356
The child you see here

03:55.444 --> 03:58.436
was a grown man
an hour before the storm hit.

03:58.948 --> 04:00.358
What happened to them?

04:00.616 --> 04:02.277
Time driven insane.

04:02.368 --> 04:04.108
The anomalies tore
through the camp,

04:04.245 --> 04:06.110
aging the survivors
hundreds of years one moment,

04:06.247 --> 04:08.203
and reversing it the next.

04:09.458 --> 04:10.618
Chaos.

04:13.087 --> 04:17.080
Temporal storms
are resurging here,
here and here.

04:17.174 --> 04:19.085
They're closing in,
destroying everything
in their path.

04:19.176 --> 04:21.337
We stopped
the paradox in 1975.

04:21.470 --> 04:22.550
It was getting
better out there.

04:22.638 --> 04:24.139
Maybe that was a coincidence.

04:25.141 --> 04:26.051
Well, none of you
seem too sure

04:26.142 --> 04:27.473
about how all of
this really works.

04:27.643 --> 04:30.601
Marcus...
I'm inclined
to agree with Mr. Whitley.

04:30.688 --> 04:33.725
Julian, we know there
was another paradox,

04:33.816 --> 04:35.477
one that we
haven't stopped yet.

04:35.609 --> 04:40.603
All the data points
to a major occurrence
between 1951 and 1973.

04:41.449 --> 04:44.566
Just one more
Primary left to save,

04:44.660 --> 04:47.026
and all this
destruction will end.

04:47.204 --> 04:48.319
Once and for all.

04:50.040 --> 04:51.029
Mr. Cole?

04:51.167 --> 04:52.782
We need to find
that Primary.

04:52.877 --> 04:56.620
I'm gonna go ask
the one person we know
who's dialed into all this.

05:02.344 --> 05:03.333
(GUN COCKS)

05:04.138 --> 05:05.173
RAMSE: Hey.

05:07.725 --> 05:08.714
Hey.

05:08.893 --> 05:09.882
You're back.

05:10.352 --> 05:11.558
How you doing?

05:12.021 --> 05:14.387
Ijust needed to get
out of here for a while.

05:14.523 --> 05:15.603
You know?

05:15.691 --> 05:16.771
You on the mend?

05:16.859 --> 05:17.848
Yeah. Yeah.

05:17.985 --> 05:20.192
Just another one
for the collection,
you know.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.611
Listen, I'm sorry that
I didn't get a Chance
to talk to you

05:23.699 --> 05:26.862
about what happened to Sam.

05:28.162 --> 05:29.151
That's all right.

05:30.539 --> 05:33.952
When we went back to the '70s,

05:34.043 --> 05:39.913
Kyle kept on bringing up
that The Witness
was from our time.

05:40.049 --> 05:42.461
That”
Yeah, he said
a lot of crazy shit.

05:42.551 --> 05:44.542
He mention
a place called Titan?

05:45.221 --> 05:47.587
"Titan"? No, never
heard of it. What is it?

05:47.723 --> 05:52.342
Cassie said that
when The Witness
was inside her head,

05:52.436 --> 05:55.724
that she was also in his.

05:57.233 --> 06:03.069
She thinks that it's a place
where he feels safe.

06:04.782 --> 06:06.067
She never
mentioned that to me.

06:07.952 --> 06:10.910
You see Jennifer,
just ask her for me.

06:11.372 --> 06:12.361
Yeah.

06:18.796 --> 06:20.536
I gotta find The Witness.

06:22.091 --> 06:23.922
I gotta make him pay.

06:24.426 --> 06:25.415
I know.

06:32.059 --> 06:33.595
(MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

06:35.938 --> 06:40.227
Primaries, plague, paradoxes

06:41.110 --> 06:43.317
and The Witness.

06:43.612 --> 06:45.648
I didn't come here
to see you do
a magic trick, Jennifer.

06:45.781 --> 06:47.146
This isn't magic.

06:47.283 --> 06:48.989
This is a lesson.

06:49.118 --> 06:51.609
Perception versus deception.

06:59.461 --> 07:05.832
Cassie, Ramse,
Katarina, her daughter,
my daughter.

07:06.176 --> 07:08.258
All of them, distractions.

07:10.264 --> 07:14.507
You keep watching the ball
when you should be
watching the hands.

07:16.979 --> 07:19.061
I'm beginning to
think you get off on this.

07:19.148 --> 07:22.311
There was a time
when you could
have known for sure.

07:22.776 --> 07:23.765
Mmm.

07:24.153 --> 07:25.142
Ah!

07:25.863 --> 07:26.978
What the hell was that for?

07:27.156 --> 07:28.521
I told you to watch the hands.

07:28.824 --> 07:29.813
Screw this.

07:30.826 --> 07:34.034
I can't tell you where
to find the last Primary
back in time.

07:34.163 --> 07:35.278
I never knew.

07:35.706 --> 07:37.242
But there's someone who does.

07:37.333 --> 07:38.698
The Tall Man.

07:39.501 --> 07:41.833
He leads the Army of
the 12 Monkeys now.

07:42.004 --> 07:43.995
How do I find him?
You and me.

07:44.214 --> 07:45.715
In 2016.

07:46.550 --> 07:48.836
You got 30 years
on all of us.

07:50.012 --> 07:51.673
You know how this ends,
don't you?

07:51.847 --> 07:55.180
A wise man once told me
there are many endings.

07:55.309 --> 07:59.177
But the right one
is the one you Choose.

08:00.981 --> 08:01.936
One more thing.

08:02.024 --> 08:03.013
Titan.

08:05.402 --> 08:06.391
JAMES: Yeah.

08:06.654 --> 08:07.643
Do you know about it?

08:07.738 --> 08:10.525
I know that
the search for Titan
only leads to death.

08:11.158 --> 08:13.945
Your friends,
their rage is blinding.

08:14.036 --> 08:15.867
You need to see
what they can't.

08:16.038 --> 08:17.653
Stay the course.

08:17.748 --> 08:19.329
Find the last Primary.

08:19.416 --> 08:21.031
Stop the paradox.

08:21.210 --> 08:23.326
Save the world, Otter Eyes.

08:28.258 --> 08:30.044
She didn't know anything.

08:30.177 --> 08:31.838
The Daughters are nomads.

08:31.929 --> 08:35.137
They've traveled
for miles and miles.
They gotta know something.

08:35.224 --> 08:36.634
Nothing, man. I'm sorry.

08:36.725 --> 08:37.840
Look, you sure
The Witness didn'tjust

08:37.935 --> 08:39.391
put this in your
head to distract you?

08:39.520 --> 08:40.976
This is the first time
you've even mentioned
it to me.

08:41.063 --> 08:42.894
Maybe I was afraid
you'd think I was crazy.

08:43.440 --> 08:44.896
JAMES: That's not what
I'm talking about.

08:45.234 --> 08:47.896
Look, we got work to finish.

08:48.070 --> 08:49.560
Mr. Cole,
the window's Closing.

08:49.863 --> 08:52.821
We will find him.
Together. Okay?

08:52.908 --> 08:54.409
As soon as we stop
the storms out there.

08:54.535 --> 08:55.820
I'm not waiting for that.

08:55.911 --> 08:58.778
You want to pay him back
for what he did
to Sam and you.

08:58.914 --> 09:00.495
I get that.
We will pay him back.

09:00.582 --> 09:01.992
First,
we need to focus on this.

09:02.084 --> 09:03.915
Focus on your mission, right?

09:04.795 --> 09:07.161
(SIGHS) Look, the Tall Man
is the only one

09:07.256 --> 09:09.417
who knows how to
stop the final paradox.

09:09.550 --> 09:11.211
I'm gonna find him,
I'm gonna make him talk.

09:11.301 --> 09:12.290
CASSIE: And then what?

09:13.929 --> 09:15.715
He's the man who
killed your father.

09:17.433 --> 09:18.889
I hope you get
your vengeance, Cole,

09:18.976 --> 09:20.762
while we all
wait here for ours.

09:22.396 --> 09:24.728
Initiate Splinter Sequence.

09:26.775 --> 09:28.436
(MACHINE POWERING UP)

09:36.618 --> 09:37.824
(MACHINE POWERING DOWN)

09:51.425 --> 09:52.710
All right, Hyenas.

09:52.801 --> 09:53.916
Listen up.

09:54.011 --> 09:55.797
We've traveled
a long ways together.

09:56.305 --> 10:00.924
Fought many battles
and won great victories.
(LAUGHTER)

10:01.018 --> 10:05.011
Now, we must fight again!
Yeah!

10:05.147 --> 10:06.227
JENNIFER: Back to business!

10:06.315 --> 10:07.930
Twelve Monkey
killing business!

10:08.025 --> 10:09.765
(LAUGHTER)
And business is what?

10:09.943 --> 10:10.898
ALL: Booming!

10:10.986 --> 10:11.975
We've done well,

10:12.154 --> 10:14.361
but now is not
the time to be resting
on our laurels.

10:14.490 --> 10:17.197
No, it's time for a re-up,
corner kids.

10:17.326 --> 10:18.315
Yeah!
Yeah!

10:20.370 --> 10:21.621
JENNIFER: Tonight's mission...

10:21.705 --> 10:24.321
(ALARM BLARING)

10:30.672 --> 10:33.084
They're here. They found us.

10:40.182 --> 10:41.513
(GRUNTING)

10:42.017 --> 10:43.348
(GUN COCKS)
(PANTING)

10:45.103 --> 10:46.092
Otter Eyes.

10:50.692 --> 10:53.855
This is mission control.

10:54.029 --> 10:55.269
JAMES: You've been busy.

10:55.364 --> 10:56.353
About time, don't you think?

10:57.366 --> 10:59.482
Take the fight to
them for a Change, right?

10:59.576 --> 11:01.532
We've got bigger
problems in 2044.

11:01.703 --> 11:02.863
Green to red?

11:03.038 --> 11:04.118
Bad to worse.

11:04.206 --> 11:05.616
Time's broken.

11:05.707 --> 11:09.074
Storms are
eating up the future,
working their way back to now.

11:09.878 --> 11:10.867
(GASPS)

11:14.424 --> 11:15.550
Oh, Shit!

11:15.884 --> 11:16.873
Peggy?

11:17.219 --> 11:20.552
I asked you to
please be careful
with the grenades.

11:20.639 --> 11:22.220
We got a discount
for a reason.

11:22.307 --> 11:23.968
This is a new level of crazy.

11:24.059 --> 11:27.893
Crazy is as crazy does,
and this crazy is
getting shit done.

11:30.232 --> 11:31.312
Him.

11:31.400 --> 11:33.766
I need to talk to him.
He has the answers I need.

11:33.986 --> 11:36.398
Yeah,
he is really well guarded.

11:36.488 --> 11:39.480
I mean, he never
leaves the house
without that guy.

11:39.575 --> 11:40.564
Jennﬁer

11:42.953 --> 11:45.069
He shouldn't be here.

11:45.163 --> 11:47.415
Relax. We're on
the same team.

11:47.833 --> 11:49.744
JENNIFER: It's okay, Vanessa.
He's family.

11:51.420 --> 11:52.830
Where did you
find them, again?

11:52.921 --> 11:54.912
You want to start
an antisocial organization,

11:55.007 --> 11:57.999
you need antisocial
personalities, right?

11:58.093 --> 12:01.335
Sprung them from
a handful of institutions.
(CHUCKLING)

12:01.430 --> 12:04.763
I mean, sure,
a few of them are
borderline personality,

12:04.850 --> 12:06.590
but very dedicated.

12:06.685 --> 12:09.267
You know, it's like The A-Team
with all Murdocks.

12:09.438 --> 12:11.053
They're like me.

12:11.148 --> 12:12.854
They're just misunderstood.

12:14.943 --> 12:17.776
Ifreed them, Ifeed them
and now I lead them.

12:19.615 --> 12:21.276
We're like family.

12:21.491 --> 12:22.992
She's our mother.

12:25.829 --> 12:27.285
Right.

12:36.298 --> 12:37.287
Oh, Hannah.

12:44.640 --> 12:46.926
I wanted to
return this to you.

12:47.017 --> 12:48.302
But it's yours.

12:48.393 --> 12:50.224
We don't have things.

12:50.312 --> 12:54.646
Mother says it has
sentimental value for you.

12:56.985 --> 13:00.477
You were born at
Lenox Hill Hospital
in New York City.

13:02.741 --> 13:08.702
My father, your grandfather,
he stitched your name on here.

13:09.081 --> 13:11.823
(CHUCKLING)
He had never stitched
a thing in his life.

13:13.502 --> 13:15.493
What about my father?

13:15.587 --> 13:16.963
What was he like?

13:17.047 --> 13:20.665
He had an overdeveloped
sense of self-preservation.

13:20.759 --> 13:22.215
And ambition.

13:22.552 --> 13:24.929
He built this machine.

13:27.057 --> 13:28.672
And I made itwork.

13:28.850 --> 13:34.345
You used science
to Change time.

13:35.065 --> 13:36.896
To save my life.

13:37.943 --> 13:41.435
I was told that when
I was a small Child,

13:41.530 --> 13:43.145
I was found
floating down a river

13:43.240 --> 13:47.529
on the back of a golden swan
that I had tamed.

13:48.412 --> 13:51.529
Now, Mother says
I was brought to her
because of you,

13:52.040 --> 13:55.532
a woman who used a machine
to Cheat death.

13:55.627 --> 13:57.083
No, to save you,

13:57.713 --> 13:59.249
my daughter.

14:00.590 --> 14:01.966
And billions.

14:02.217 --> 14:04.629
I like the swan story better.

14:05.053 --> 14:06.384
No one dies.

14:08.223 --> 14:10.384
Science killed the world.

14:10.475 --> 14:13.558
Now, your machine is
going to finish off
what's left of us.

14:16.773 --> 14:20.436
This is every record
we have, and no mention
of Titan anywhere.

14:20.777 --> 14:22.438
Maybe Cole was right.

14:22.571 --> 14:24.812
Maybe it's not real.

14:24.948 --> 14:26.609
You said you felt it.

14:26.908 --> 14:27.943
Yes.

14:28.452 --> 14:29.567
He's there.

14:29.786 --> 14:31.287
We just gotta keep looking.

14:32.164 --> 14:34.997
(SIGHS) Ramse,
even if this place exists,

14:35.083 --> 14:36.539
it could be
anywhere in the world,

14:36.626 --> 14:40.118
and we don't
have maps or records
from after the plague.

14:40.255 --> 14:43.042
What we need is something
that doesn't exist in 2044.

14:43.133 --> 14:46.500
We need
a database of some kind.

14:47.345 --> 14:48.334
Hannah?

14:49.014 --> 14:50.424
What is a database?

14:51.141 --> 14:54.850
It's a place where
information is collected
and stored.

14:55.312 --> 14:56.802
Like The Keeper.

14:57.022 --> 14:58.011
What's that?

14:58.106 --> 14:59.095
He's like your database.

14:59.191 --> 15:00.431
He collects information.

15:00.984 --> 15:03.270
The history of what happened
after the old ones died.

15:03.987 --> 15:05.227
Can you take us to him?

15:05.322 --> 15:06.812
He can be dangerous.

15:06.948 --> 15:09.155
Mother has forbidden us
from trading with The Keeper,

15:09.284 --> 15:11.149
but I could tell
you how to get there.

15:11.703 --> 15:13.284
What does he trade in?

15:15.332 --> 15:16.492
Truth.

15:20.462 --> 15:21.451
(BLOWS)

15:21.838 --> 15:23.544
You're not going alone.

15:23.673 --> 15:26.460
You're concerned
for my safety now?
No.

15:27.469 --> 15:29.300
But I know that
ifyou figure out
where The Witness is,

15:29.387 --> 15:30.718
you're not coming back for me.

15:30.806 --> 15:32.012
Get outta here.

15:32.140 --> 15:34.005
You're not the only
one out for blood.

15:35.143 --> 15:36.679
The Witness used me.

15:36.812 --> 15:39.519
Keeper isn't
the only dangerous
thing out there.

15:39.648 --> 15:42.230
You're not immune,
and it's a long drive.

15:44.694 --> 15:45.900
Shotgun.

15:50.492 --> 15:54.531
PALLID MAN: These Hyenas
burned six of our labs.
Now we have nothing.

15:54.871 --> 15:57.283
That's him.
How did you get this?

15:57.374 --> 16:00.411
We left him a phone,
so he'd know who's
been screwing with him.

16:00.502 --> 16:02.117
He used it?
No.

16:02.212 --> 16:03.201
But he kept it.

16:03.380 --> 16:04.460
Didn't know we'd Chipped it.

16:04.548 --> 16:07.085
So anytime he's here,
we get stuff like this.
Listen.

16:07.175 --> 16:09.257
PALLID MAN: We cannot proceed
without Oliver Peters.

16:09.678 --> 16:13.341
The virus was destroyed.
He’s the only who
can recreate it.

16:14.057 --> 16:15.172
We need M510.

16:15.267 --> 16:16.256
Peters.

16:16.518 --> 16:20.431
AKA the guy who
created the virus
that kills us all.

16:20.522 --> 16:21.853
We've been looking for him.

16:21.940 --> 16:23.305
Cassie told him to
get out of Dodge.

16:23.400 --> 16:24.731
He's long gone by now.

16:25.068 --> 16:26.057
Or is he?

16:26.403 --> 16:27.734
Peters was adopted.

16:27.821 --> 16:30.483
My father helped track down
his birth parents.

16:30.574 --> 16:33.486
They were dead,
but there was a brother.

16:33.577 --> 16:36.660
After Peters disappeared,
so did his money.

16:36.746 --> 16:38.737
And that long-lost brother

16:38.832 --> 16:44.247
goes from a studio in Flatbush
to six bedrooms in Sag Harbor.

