Not a lot to go on.

36:42.993 --> 36:45.405
A name, a place and a date.

36:45.954 --> 36:46.943
Put them together.

36:47.664 --> 36:49.325
And we've got a new mission.

36:49.500 --> 36:51.081
There ain't no "we",
lady.

36:51.168 --> 36:55.502
The only one who
wants The Witness dead
as much as you is me.

36:57.091 --> 36:58.251
(THUNDER RUMBLING)
Here.

36:58.842 --> 37:01.333
I don't need another partner
with a death wish.

37:12.648 --> 37:13.637
(SNIFFS)

37:15.984 --> 37:16.973
(SNIFFLES)

37:23.283 --> 37:24.363
Hey.

37:27.371 --> 37:29.783
Wasn't sure what
you wanted to do
with this little guy.

37:32.042 --> 37:33.202
Jerry?

37:34.545 --> 37:36.536
I can't take care of him.

37:38.382 --> 37:40.122
(SOBBING) I can't
take care of anything.

37:40.217 --> 37:43.050
Listen, I know how you feel.

37:43.637 --> 37:44.717
Okay?
(SNIFFLES)

37:45.305 --> 37:47.387
This is the price
of taking people on.

37:50.144 --> 37:51.884
But I didn't pay it.

37:53.063 --> 37:55.179
They didn't deserve to die.

37:55.816 --> 37:58.728
I made them Hyenas.

37:59.903 --> 38:01.643
They were my fault.

38:03.907 --> 38:06.569
(CRYING) And all
the people in the hospital.

38:07.035 --> 38:09.412
(SNIFFLING)
Hundreds of people.

38:10.372 --> 38:12.784
Cole, is this what
I become in the future?

38:12.875 --> 38:15.491
A woman who's failed everyone?

38:16.086 --> 38:17.075
No.

38:18.589 --> 38:21.831
Then tell me what happens.
How does this end?

38:27.431 --> 38:29.342
There are many endings.

38:31.018 --> 38:32.599
Which is the right one?

38:34.938 --> 38:36.519
The right one

38:36.773 --> 38:39.025
is the one you choose.
Is the one you Choose.

38:43.614 --> 38:44.603
(GROANS)

38:47.701 --> 38:48.941
Time to go?

38:49.077 --> 38:50.613
See you soon.

38:53.874 --> 38:54.863
(SNIFFLES)

38:55.542 --> 38:56.782
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

39:07.137 --> 39:09.219
Wow. You weren't kidding.

39:10.891 --> 39:12.381
Jennﬁer

39:21.860 --> 39:24.101
You must be Hannah.

39:29.868 --> 39:31.404
If you'll excuse me...

39:31.870 --> 39:34.202
JUHan.JuHan.

39:37.376 --> 39:38.866
Should I not be here?

39:39.878 --> 39:43.746
For many years,
Dr. Adler and I
shared a common bond.

39:44.758 --> 39:46.544
The loss of a Child.

39:47.553 --> 39:49.418
And now that's Changed.

39:50.264 --> 39:52.425
I didn't mean to
offend you earlier.

39:52.599 --> 39:55.056
Mother says
most people are not
accustomed to directness.

39:55.602 --> 39:58.093
I don't really
understand why not but...
Hannah.

39:58.272 --> 40:00.558
There's so much
that we don't know
about each other.

40:00.649 --> 40:03.891
I'd rather not
waste any more time
with pretty lies.

40:05.612 --> 40:09.571
(CHUCKLES) Ijust realized
"Hannah" might not be

40:09.658 --> 40:12.274
the name that
Jennifer calls you.

40:12.786 --> 40:14.617
She's always called me Zeit.

40:15.289 --> 40:17.325
Zeit. (CHUCKLES)

40:17.583 --> 40:19.824
That's German.
You know what that means?

40:21.253 --> 40:22.914
It means "time."

40:23.672 --> 40:24.661
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

40:25.090 --> 40:27.251
Mother is not
without her sense of humor.

40:28.135 --> 40:29.170
Oh.

40:29.303 --> 40:31.669
You asked me
about your father.

40:36.476 --> 40:38.467
I think he looks like you.

40:39.521 --> 40:41.136
He was quite
a brilliant man.

40:41.273 --> 40:42.979
He only ever
gave me two things.

40:43.108 --> 40:44.518
This machine and you.

40:46.653 --> 40:49.440
But you were the only thing
lever loved him for.

40:51.283 --> 40:52.614
Thank you.

40:55.662 --> 40:59.325
If you like,
you may call me Hannah.

41:04.338 --> 41:07.000
ELLIOT: Another
brilliant mind lost.

41:08.342 --> 41:10.173
I know what that's like.

41:10.302 --> 41:11.417
'Cause I could
have been the man

41:11.511 --> 41:13.502
that science
mistook for a magician.

41:13.639 --> 41:18.258
Me and Tesla
and Ben Franklin
and his kite, you know.

41:18.352 --> 41:20.138
But nope, 'Cause
they pull your funding.

41:20.479 --> 41:23.016
They find one dead body
in your facility and...

41:23.148 --> 41:24.433
(IMITATES EXPLOSION)
They mothball the future.

41:24.524 --> 41:26.776
And then they discredit you.
(SCOFFS)

41:26.860 --> 41:28.725
And I'm not dead,
but I might as well be.

41:37.412 --> 41:40.324
Do you believe in
resurrection, Doctor?

41:41.500 --> 41:44.992
Man, I'm afraid
I've become a realist
in my failed state.

41:45.087 --> 41:48.875
Enough to know that
this idea that you're
talking about is impossible.

41:49.007 --> 41:50.122
How so?

41:50.217 --> 41:53.129
The technology
doesn't exist, man.
It would take...

41:53.220 --> 41:55.836
I don't know, shit, decades.

41:56.556 --> 41:58.968
Unless you, you know...

41:59.059 --> 42:01.220
Regardless,
let me ask you something.

42:01.311 --> 42:06.055
Even if I could
build this for you,
why would you want it?

42:06.650 --> 42:07.856
Insurance.

42:08.193 --> 42:09.649
(SCOFFS) Against what?

42:10.070 --> 42:11.480
The future.

42:11.738 --> 42:13.649
(CHUCKLING) Huh.

42:19.413 --> 42:21.404
This project is massive.

42:21.707 --> 42:22.867
It is.

42:28.839 --> 42:30.875
That's why we're
calling it Titan.
